1960 - 2017 | Yearly | % | World Bank

Malawi MW: Population: as % of Total: Female: Aged 0-14 data was reported at 43.229 % in 2017. This records a decrease from the previous number of 43.520 % for 2016. Malawi MW: Population: as % of Total: Female: Aged 0-14 data is updated yearly, averaging 45.422 % from Dec 1960 (Median) to 2017, with 58 observations. The data reached an all-time high of 46.585 % in 1985 and a record low of 42.911 % in 1965. Malawi MW: Population: as % of Total: Female: Aged 0-14 data remains active status in CEIC and is reported by World Bank. The data is categorized under Global Database’s Malawi – Table MW.World Bank.WDI: Population and Urbanization Statistics. Female population between the ages 0 to 14 as a percentage of the total female population.
